<section class="section-tight" aria-labelledby="news-title">
  <div class="container">
    <article class="card announcement">
      <div>
        <div class="announcement-eyebrow">Brussels, 10 October 2025</div>
        <h2 id="news-title">EISS launches major initiative to network European Security Studies</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Thanks to the generous support of the
          <a href="https://www.cost.eu" target="_blank" rel="noopener">European Cooperation in Science and Technology</a>
          (COST) organisation, EISS — together with a dozen institutions throughout Europe — launches
          <a href="https://netsec-cost.eu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">“Networking European Security Knowledge” (NetSec)</a>,
          a four-year programme to address the fragmentation of the continent’s intellectual and
          analytical base in the field of security studies.
        </p>
        <p>
          Dr Hugo Meijer, Founding Director of EISS, and Dr Marie Robin, EISS Treasurer, serve as
          NetSec Action Chair and Vice-Chair, respectively.
        </p>

        <blockquote class="pullquote">
          “The launch of NetSec is a huge step in the development of EISS and its partners.
          Watch out for policy workshops, summer schools and conferences in the next four years.”
          <cite>— Dr Hugo Meijer, NetSec Action Chair and Founding Director of EISS</cite>
        </blockquote>

        <div>
          <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="https://netsec-cost.eu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            Learn more about NetSec
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <figure class="announcement-figure">
        <img src="/assets/images/1760518013943-1280x720.jpg"
             alt="Members of the NetSec Management Committee at the launch event in Brussels."
             loading="lazy"
             width="1280" height="720">
        <figcaption>
